Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Mix graham crumbs, butter and 3 Tbsp. sugar; press onto bottom of 13x9-inch pan. Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla with mixer until well blended. Add eggs; mix just until blended. Pour over crust. Bake 30 min. or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours. Cut into bars. Decorate with gels and sprinkles to resemble presents.